          <span id="2" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          Areas of proteins which contain amino acids with polar side groups.
          <span id="3" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          This atom is present in proteins, but not many other food components. It can therefore be used to analyse foods for protein content.
          <span id="4" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
