        <p>
          An example of a digestive enzyme which cleaves peptide bonds.
          <span id="7" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          The type of bonds which cause the formation of α helices and β sheets.
          <span id="8" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          The type of structure to which α helices, β sheets, and turns are referred.
          <span id="9" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          The overall structure of a protein.
          <span id="10" class="tiny button radius secondary">?</span>
        </p>
        <p>
